    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-30T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/395: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-30T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >September 30, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As published <persName corresp="#p_KGB1">General Klinger</persName>’s plan to
                        <persName corresp="#p_VGD1">Getulio Vargas</persName> requesting armistice
                    sent at 1 o’clock a.m. September 29 reads in translation: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“With the object of sparing the nation further sacrifices of life and
                            material losses the command of the Constitutionalist forces proposes
                            immediate suspension hostilities on all fronts for the purpose arranging
                            measures for the cessation of armed strife.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In response Dictator directed negotiate with <persName corresp="#p_GMGPA1"
                        >General Goes Monteiro</persName>, emissary of São Paulo meeting <persName
                        corresp="#p_GMGPA1">Monteiro</persName> in the vicinity Lorena evening 29th.
                    Terms offered are not known yet. Civil government heads have issued a statement
                    that they will remain in office until definite peace arrangements concluded.
                    Police and soldiers at posts here, suburbs patrolled but many Paulistas
                    resentful <persName corresp="#p_KGB1">Klinger</persName>’s action claiming
                    military situation not yet hopeless and should terms of peace offered be
                    humiliating some reaction may be expected. A considerable number political and
                    radical prisoners were released last night. Situation tense.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
